github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/14285206","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/1257#issuecomment-14285206","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1257","id":14285206,"user":{"login":"jancborchardt","id":925062,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f84ec51f9ceed468217d4e13abf78da9c.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"2fd3f4d5d762955e5b603794a888fa97","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt","html_url":"https://github.com/jancborchardt","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jancborchardt/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-01t11:38:39z","updated_at":"2013-03-01t11:38:55z","body":"thatâ€™s what i meant by â»if for security it should be fixed differentlyâ«. how exactly can the server be killed by misusing the feature? too many files, too many subsequent downloads? that should then be blocked automatically (with notice) instead of having a zip-killswitch. cc @lukasreschke "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/14384034","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/1257#issuecomment-14384034","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1257","id":14384034,"user":{"login":"juanjfr","id":3331922,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/703eb8fb1e91b4b627a8320b5e015f61?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f5233534605755e3906356bb8c66cc03b.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"703eb8fb1e91b4b627a8320b5e015f61","url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr","html_url":"https://github.com/juanjfr","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/juanjfr/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-04t14:50:01z","updated_at":"2013-03-04t14:52:14z","body":"hello,\r\n\r\nour family server for example, an atom cpu server, if somebody click to zip a folder with 2gb of data, the cpu hangs the server until the operation is finished. and this is a few minutes operation whith an atom cpu. \r\n\r\nof course with better cpus this can not happen. but perhaps, a community mid range server, i3 for example, if it gets 10 requests to zip the same 4 gb folder can hang too.\r\n\r\nthis is why we need it :)\r\n\r\n\r\nps. still happening with 4.5.7"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/15551358","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/1257#issuecomment-15551358","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1257","id":15551358,"user":{"login":"martinsauter","id":3988874,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/0e468e372e71709aced396b269babc69?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f3e031d1a3191f4738d48dc080cb6c87e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"0e468e372e71709aced396b269babc69","url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter","html_url":"https://github.com/martinsauter","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-27t20:34:23z","updated_at":"2013-03-27t20:34:23z","body":"> if i disable \"zip downloads\" from admin panel, then the shared folder dont work for \r\n> individual downloads. jpg previews work, but when try to download go to login page, and \r\n> after login says that cloud not found.\r\n> enablilng \"zip downloads\" then the same folder work for downloads.\r\n\r\nhaving exactly the same problem here and indeed it is fixed by enabling zip downloads. once done, individual files can be downloaded again with the download button next to a file name. thanks for the error description, spent hours trying to figure out why this has \"suddenly\" stopped working without getting to the bottom of it.\r\n\r\nside note: if zip download is disabled then clicking on \"download\" at individual files goes to \"cloud not found\". interestingly enough, when right clicking on a filename and then clicking on \"save link as\" downloads the file o.k.\r\n\r\nupgraded to oc 5.0 (and encountering + fixing the file sharing issue and upgrading issue with firefox) but the problem is still present.\r\n\r\nwould be nice if this could be fixed in oc 5.0.x as i am running oc on a raspberry pi which it requires considerable time ziping large files."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/15894181","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/1257#issuecomment-15894181","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1257","id":15894181,"user":{"login":"martinsauter","id":3988874,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/0e468e372e71709aced396b269babc69?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f3e031d1a3191f4738d48dc080cb6c87e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"0e468e372e71709aced396b269babc69","url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter","html_url":"https://github.com/martinsauter","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinsauter/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-04-04t12:26:33z","updated_at":"2013-04-04t12:26:33z","body":"with oc 4.5.8 a workaround is available: starting with this version the \"maximum input size for zip files\" in the admin setting now works. if set to a low value (e.g. 10 mb) and the directory that is shared contains files exceeding this size, the zip download button is not shown."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/22270416","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/1257#issuecomment-22270416","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/1257","id":22270416,"user":{"login":"jancborchardt","id":925062,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/2fd3f4d5d762955e